ENTRY       EC 2.4.1.253                Enzyme
NAME        baicalein 7-O-glucuronosyltransferase;
            UBGAT
CLASS       Transferases;
            Glycosyltransferases;
            Hexosyltransferases
SYSNAME     UDP-D-glucuronate:5,6,7-trihydroxyflavone 7-O-glucuronosyltransferase
REACTION    UDP-D-glucuronate + baicalein = UDP + baicalin [RN:R09529]
ALL_REAC    R09529
SUBSTRATE   UDP-D-glucuronate [CPD:C00167];
            baicalein [CPD:C10023]
PRODUCT     UDP [CPD:C00015];
            baicalin [CPD:C10025]
COMMENT     The enzyme is specific for UDP-D-glucuronate as a sugar donor and flavones with substitution ortho- to the 7-OH group such as baicalein (6-OH), scutellarein (6-OH) and wogonin (8-OMe).
